
Overview of verb spare

The verb spare has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (7) spare, save -- (refrain from harming)
2. (5) spare -- (save or relieve from an experience or action; "I'll spare you from having to apologize formally")
3. (5) spare, give up, part with, dispense with -- (give up what is not strictly needed; "he asked if they could spare one of their horses to speed his journey")
4. spare -- (use frugally or carefully)
